author: Paramount Plus
description:
Hip Hop Was Born Here is a Hip-Hop themed documentary series hosted by LL COOL J. The series will go beyond what you think you know to explore the creation, the evolution, and the ongoing legacy that Hip-Hop culture has cemented into our modern society. As we celebrated the 50th anniversary in 2023, the legendary LL COOL J will document how Hip-Hop has become more than a genre. It's a culture. 

We will meet OGs and future icons, visit the neighborhoods. Studios, and places that fostered early styles, and watch beloved artists analyze their favorite tracks. The show will follow LL COOL J as he travels through Hip-Hop history, highlighting the most important songs, performers, and cultural influences that shaped the genre into the sensation that it is today.
